
RDMA - Direct memory access (DMA) is an ability of a device to access host memory directly, without the intervention of the CPU(s). 
 
 there are several network protocols which support RDMA: 
 
Infiniband - a new generation network protocol which supports RDMA natively from the beginning. Since this is a new network technology, it requires NICs and switches which supports this technology. 
 
RoCE - RoCE protocols define how to perform RDMA using Ethernet and UDP/IP frames 
 
IWARP -  iWARP protocol defines how to perform RDMA over a connection-oriented transport like the Transmission Control Protocol (TCP) 
 
 
